<HEADLINE> UNDP Joins Women's Leadership Initiative in Latin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) is participating in a U.N. inter-agency
program to increase the number of women in policy-making and
leadership roles in Latin America and the Caribbean, the UNDP said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The program, entitled Program for the Support of Womem's
Leadership and Representation, aims to enhance the participation
of women in all levels of public life.
</P>
<P>
It will also foster regional women's networks and strengthen
organizations that work to increase opportunities for women.
</P>
<P>
Initiatives will include leadership skills training for women,
public education and legislative reform.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP's Regional Bureau for Latin America and the Caribbean
is providing 400,000 U.S. dollars. Partners include the
Inter-Agency Development Bank, the United Nations Children's Fund
and the non-governmental organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
