<HEADLINE> Vogts Wants More Young Faces in Bundesliga </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Germany coach Berti Vogts has
urged the Bundesliga clubs to make use of young players to ensure
the nation's place among football powerhouses in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Vogts said he wants to see each club has at least one player
aged below 23 on the pitch for each game.
</P>
<P>
The manager complained that he was alarmed and saddened at the
absence of new blood in the current German national team.
</P>
<P>
The German team are here for tonight's World Cup warm-up match
with Finland. 
</P>
