<HEADLINE> Morocco Takes Lead in MicroStart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Morocco has become the first
of 25 developing countries to receive assistance through an
international microcredit initiative to expand small-scale lending
and financial programs, the UNDP said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
MicroStart, a UNDP global pilot program, helps local
institutions provide credit and financial services to the poor.
</P>
<P>
In Morocco, the 150,000 U.S. dollars provided by MicroStart
helps to strengthen the human, financial and technical resources
at four community lending organizations, and enable them to expand
credit and financial services to small business operators.
</P>
<P>
In just four months since receiving the assistance, these
institutions were able to make an additional 600 small loans, many
to women in rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
