<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Falls 97.87 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay
Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday closed at 3777.19 as against
Tuesday's close of 3875.06, showing a net fall of 97.87 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index dropped by 37.37 points to 1684.87 from the
previous close of 1722.24.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted remarkably
down at 383.87 and 154.75 compared with Tuesday's close of 390.90
and 158.23 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities suffered a sharp setback bringing the sensitive index
down by over 97 points on the stock market Wednesday in the wake
of bull liquidation and heavy selling by foreign funds triggered
by the World Bank decision to put off talks on India loans.
</P>
