<DOCNO> XIE19980528.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Exchange Index Drops Dramatically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index went into another fall Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 Index lost 70.64 points to close at 1092.86 points
Wednesday against Tuesday's close of 1163.50 points.
</P>
<P>
A total turnover of 50.10 million shares were traded Wednesday
against 810,000 shares traded the previous day.
</P>
<P>
There were 20 gainers, 86 losers while 32 scrips remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Within an hour of trading, the Karachi Automated Trading
System, the computer system on which the bourse trades, developed
some problems and trading was suspended till the afternoon
session.
</P>
<P>
On resumption of business, the news that the government has
appealed to the Lahore High Court (LHC) to order the Hub Power
Company Limited (Hubco) to bring back money it has repatriated as
profits abroad was greeted with heavy selling in most stocks.
</P>
<P>
The LHC has set June 2 as the next date for hearing of the case
in which a private citizen has challenged the rate at which Hubco
is charging the government in power tariffs.
</P>
<P>
The case has caused upsets on the market since the court has
decreed that till the hearing is concluded, Hubco will have to
sell power at 1.50 Pakistani rupee (PKR) per kilowatt hour (KWH)
against the existing rate of over five PKR per KWH (one U.S.
dollar=44.05 PKR).
</P>
<P>
Traders expect further falls in the Karachi Stock market in the
absence of any good news or positive indicators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
