<HEADLINE> Belarussian Prime Minister Visits Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian Prime Minister Sergei
Stepanovich Ling arrived here on Wednesday for a three-day
official visit aimed at boosting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
"My visit offers us the opportunity to examine our relations,
which are already developed," Ling told reporters upon arrival at
Larnaca Airport.
</P>
<P>
"I am sure that after this visit our relations will develop
even further and will reach a high level," he added.
</P>
<P>
Cypriot Minister of Commerce, Industry and Tourism Nicos
Rolandis, who greeted Ling at the airport for President Glafcos
Clerides, described the political relations between Cyprus and
Belarus as "very good," saying the prime minister's visit will
offer an opportunity to enhance the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Issues of cooperation in trade, economy, air transport and
tourism will be discussed between the two sides, Rolandis said.
</P>
<P>
According to Cypriot officials, Cyprus and Belarus will sign
three agreements on avoidance of double taxation, promotion and
reciprocal protection of investments and air services during
Ling's visit. 
