<HEADLINE> Britain Realizes Grave Situation after Indian Nuclear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 27 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said on Wednesday that Britain fully realizes the grave and
precarious situation which has been created as a result of the
Indian nuclear explosions.
</P>
<P>
Blair made the remarks in yet another telephone conversation he
had with his Pakistani counterpart Nawaz Sharif, according to
sources from the secretariat of the prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said that the Indian action has been widely condemned
the world over and India today stands isolated in the
international community.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders exchanged views on the situation emerging in
the wake of the Indian nuclear explosions and their fall-out for
the countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
"Britain fully realizes the grave and precarious situation
which has been created as a result of the Indian explosions and
which exposes the whole region to instability," the British prime
minister said.
</P>
<P>
The British prime minister had earlier talked with Sharif twice
over telephone exchanging views on the situation in the region
after the Indian nuclear tests. 
</P>
