<HEADLINE> Bonn Approves Continued Peace Mission in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The German cabinet has approved an
extension of German soldiers' peacekeeping mission in Bosnia, a
government spokesman announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the Bonn government has also
decided that Germany's contributions to the U.N. peacekeeping
forces in Bosnia, the Stabilization Force (SFOR), will remain at
the current level of 3,000 soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The current mandate of the 35,000 SFOR troops in Bosnia is due
to expire on June 19. Germany has said that it supports an
extension of the mandate and believes that European countries
should maintain their troop contribution at the current levels
though the number of U.S. soldiers is likely to be reduced.
</P>
<P>
According to German Defense Minister Volker Ruehe, the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) is expected to make a decision
on the Bosnia peace operation Thursday. 
</P>
