<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-27 17:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Succeeds in Setting up Own Oil Refining Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran said Wednesday its engineers
have succeeded in setting up its own oil catalytic cracking unit
to produce motor gasoline on Lavan island in the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA reported that the unit, to be
operational within one year, would be capable of producing 3,000
barrels of gasoline and 500 barrels of liquid gas per day.
</P>
<P>
It said construction of the catalytic cracking unit started in
1993, and 75 percent of it has been completed so far.
</P>
<P>
Foreign companies had put the price of the project at 77
million U.S. dollars, but Iranian experts estimated the actual
cost at 30 million dollars, IRNA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
