<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian PM Speaks on Relations With U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Russia has good working relations
with the United States, Russian Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko
said here at the Congress of the 47th General Assembly of the
International Press Institute (IPI) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The premier said the Intergovernmental Commission on Trade and
Technological Cooperation between the two countries, which has
done a lot of good over the past five years, will meet in Moscow,
and its date is to be set soon.
</P>
<P>
Russia will maintain mutually beneficial cooperation with other
countries but will never deviate from the commitments under the
agreement on non-proliferation of nuclear technologies, Kiriyenko
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the recent events in Latvia amount to violations of the
Russian-speaking population's rights. Russia cannot be indifferent
to this and will take "civilized steps to influence the situation
and prevent the violation of the rights of ethnic Russians, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Stressing the protection of human rights is a major priority in
the government's activities, Kiriyenko said the Russian
authorities will do their best to prevent any incidents in the
country which could be regarded as a violation of human rights.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the congress of the IPI, Kiriyenko also emphasized
the problem of stabilization in Russia. He said that "efficient
social welfare" is the key to stabilization of the country.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Efficient social welfare is a crucial element of
stabilizing the general situation in Russia." The efficiency of
social welfare can be achieved only by adopting a firm financial
policy, he added.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko stressed that the government will invest maximum
efforts to ensure that social welfare reaches the destination.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
