<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Decrees to Set Up Military Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Wednesday signed a decree to set up a State Commission for
Military Construction, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The main task of the commission is to prepare programs for
military construction made by the president. Meanwhile, the
function of the commission's working organs will be ensured by the
Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko was appointed chairman of the
commission. Its members include First Deputy Prime Minister Boris
Nemtsov, Secretary of the Security Council Andrei Kokoshin and
Chief of the General Staff of the Russian Armed Forces Anatoly
Kvashnin. 
</P>
