<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Susan McDougal to Be Tried for Embezzlement in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 27 (Xinhua) -- A judge in Santa Monica,
California, Wednesday set a July 13 trial date for Susan McDougal
on charges she embezzled 150,000 dollars from conductor Zubin
Mehta and his wife while she worked as their bookkeeper.
</P>
<P>
The Whitewater figure didn't make it to court because she
wasn't feeling well, so Superior Court Judge Steven Suzukawa
decided to set the date without her, the Associated Press
reported.
</P>
<P>
Defense attorney Mark Geragos said he was uncertain of his
client's ailment. He said she had seen a doctor.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. McDougal was charged with grand theft, check forgery,
fraudulent use of credit cards, income tax evasion and making
false financial statements, from 1989 to 1992.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. McDougal and then-husband Jim McDougal were partners in
the failed Whitewater development with Bill and Hillary Rodham
Clinton when Bill Clinton was governor of Arkansas. Both McDougals
were convicted of bank fraud.
</P>
<P>
Jim McDougal died in a Texas federal prison on March 8.
</P>
<P>
Geragos said Mrs. McDougal will face another trial in Little
Rock, Arkansas, before the Santa Monica trial. A jury trial is
scheduled for June 22 on two counts of criminal contempt and one
count of obstruction of justice for her refusal to testify before
the Whitewater grand jury.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. McDougal served 18 months for civil contempt in a jail
term imposed to coerce her cooperation with the grand jury. That
term expired in March and she has served time since then on her
two-year Whitewater prison sentence for fraud. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
