<HEADLINE> 400 Million Dollars Needed to Rebuild Turkey's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 27 (Xinhua) -- A total of 412 million U.S. dollars
is needed to reconstruct Turkey's northwestern region hit by
floods last week.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters at the National Crisis Administration
Center, Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz said that the money
will be used to repair highways, bridges as well as civilian
houses.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz said that the government has worked out an action plan
to help rebuild the deluge-stricken provinces, such as Bartin,
Bolu, Zonguldak and Karaduk.
</P>
<P>
The plan will be presented to the National Crisis
Administration Center soon, he added.
</P>
<P>
The unprecedented floods hitting northwestern Turkey claimed 19
lives and left eight others missing, and caused huge economic
losses.
</P>
<P>
Turkish government and the Red Crescent Association have sent
supplies, including mobile kitchens, tents and blankets, to the
flood-stricken areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
