<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 28 (Xinhua) -- FIFA Secretary General Sepp Blatter
ruled out any possibilities of remaining on duty if his rival
Leonnart Johansson won the FIFA presidential election on June 8.
</P>
<P>
Asked by French magazine "French Football" whether he would
work out any agreement with the UEFA President that would keep
both of them on the world football governing after the election,
the Swiss said he did not think so.
</P>
<P>
