<HEADLINE> China's 1st Electrified High-Speed Railway Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The construction of China's first
electrified high-speed railway, from Guangzhou to Shenzhen in
southern Guangdong Province, was completed today. It is the
speediest in the country.
</P>
<P>
The railway was built by the Railway Ministry and the Guangzhou
and Shenzhen Railway Joint Stock Co. Ltd., with an investment of
700 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
By June 10, when the railway is fully electrified, a new
locomotive from Sweden will make test-runs on the tracks at 200 km
per hour.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of the railway and the use of the Swedish
locomotive, it will merely take 48 minutes from Guangzhou to
Shenzhen, as against the present 65 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the time between Guangdong and Kowloon, Hong
Kong, will also be shortened from 105 minutes to 88 minutes.
</P>
</TEXT>
