<HEADLINE> Beijing Modernizing 100-Year-Old Commercial Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital began work on a
construction project today to modernize Wangfujing Street, a
100-year-old busy commercial artery in its downtown area.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, 350,000 sq.m. of commercial space has
been built in the area, and a million sq. m. more is being built,
a local official said.
</P>
<P>
But, infrastructure and public facilities are still backward,
and the construction speed is rather slow, the official says. So,
the municipal government will spend 100 million yuan on ten
underground pipes and cables along the 810-meter street, he said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the city will plant trees and build more
public facilities on both sides of the street, like small squares,
fountains, flower beds, sculptures, and benches.  
