<HEADLINE> Macao Lawyer Says He's Confident About Macao's Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, May 28 (Xinhua) -- As the return of Macao to China
draws near, Leonel Allerto Alves, a Portuguese man who was born in
Macao, says that he is confident about Macao's future and will
dedicate his knowledge of the law to the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Alves has a law practice in Macao and was made a member of the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
There are about 10,000 Portuguese who were born in Macao who
have formed a special group and have deep feelings for Macao. "Our
roots are in Macao. We love Macao and are ready to contribute to
its future," Alves says.
</P>
<P>
Many Portuguese who were born here are civil servants or work
in the culture, legal, educational, and medical sectors. Some have
been elected into the Macao SAR Preparatory Committee and say they
want to play an active part in the transition and transfer of
power and will work together with other residents of Macao to
greet Macao's return.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Preparatory Committee are cooperating and are
looking at all the crucial questions relating to Macao's return,
Alves says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
