<HEADLINE> China's Real Estate Business Hits New High In April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate had recovered
from a year of stagnation by last month, the State Statistics
Bureau and China Business Climate Monitoring Center reported today.
</P>
<P>
The China Real Estate Business Climate Index, which guages
activity in the sector, hit 100.81 points in April, the highest
point for the previous 11 months.
</P>
<P>
The April index is 1.76 points higher than for March, and 2.56
points higher than for a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The sector had 52.1 billion yuan in business in the first four
months of this year, up 12.7 percent from the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
New real estate projects were adding 34.78 million square
meters, up 44 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Housing prices were up on a monthly basis since the beginning
of this year, from 2,091 yuan in February to 2,258 yuan in April.
</P>
