community Thursday to speed up the process of seeking a solution
to the crisis of his country.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival in Tehran, Secretary General of the Afghan
Islamic Unity Party Mohammad Karim Khalili called for closer
cooperation between the United Nations and the Organization of the
Islamic Conference (OIC) to help end the Afghan civil war.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran, the current OIC chairman and a neighbor of
Afghanistan, is able to play a key role in helping solve the
Afghan problem and establish peace and stability in the country.
</P>
