affairs Alaeddin Boroujerdi said that Iran, despite all
obstacles, supports the continuation of the Afghan peace process
and the peace talks participated by all Afghan groups.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the need for OIC-U.N. cooperation to speed up
peace process between Afghanistan's belligerent factions, saying
that Tehran will do all it can to help establish peace.
</P>
<P>
The Afghan peace talks were deadlocked earlier this month
between the Taliban and its rival Northern Alliance headed by
ousted President Burhanuddin Rabbani, who was driven out of the
capital Kabul by the Taliban militia in September, 1996. 
