<HEADLINE> China Opens Financial Information Service System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- A comprehensive financial
information system was officially put into service today,
marking a big stride forward for China's financial industry in its
electronics and information service.
</P>
<P>
The newly-commissioned National Bank Governor Information
Service System is a part of the National Financial Information
Service Network (NFISN), which has been jointly sponsored by a
number of financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the NFISN said the network has so far established
five core systems covering banking information, security
investment information, insurance information and enterprise
financial information, as well as a central information databank.
The network uses various modern service measures to provide users
with comprehensive financial information.
</P>
<P>
As the most important component of the network, the National
Bank Governor Information Service System collects information from
authoritative financial institutions, security companies and other
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Users of the system mainly include branches of the People's
Bank of China at various levels, the State Administration of
Foreign Exchange, commercial banks and other financial
institutions.  
</P>
