<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Bank of China Enforcing Financial Order </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hubei branch of the People's
Bank of China (PBOC) penalized 6 financial institutions and 26
individuals earlier this week for failing to comply with finance
laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
This closely followed the central bank's penalizing the
directors of 8 other financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
This year, the bank has worked to improve financial order
during the period of reforms to eliminate financial risks.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the financial sector say that finance departments
have looked into various kinds of malpractice in business and
local departments have paid attention off-the-record operations,
paying high interest for deposits, using public funds for private
benefit, and improper cash management.
</P>
<P>
Financial institutions are also trying to improve internal
controls. According to PBOC rules and regulations, if any
financial institution is found guilty of serious malpractices, the
director and employees face the risk of losing their jobs.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, PBOC's governor, said recently that the new
round of financial reforms benefits financial developments and
improves employee quality, and that good financial order is a
significant part of the reforms.  
</P>
</TEXT>
