<HEADLINE> Woman Gets Death Penalty For Children-Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The First Intermediate People's
Court of Chongqing Municipality, in southwest China, today
sentenced a children-trafficker Yan Guangfen to death and deprived
her of properties valued at 50,000 yuan at a public gathering.
</P>
<P>
Yan was executed soon after the announcement was made. Yan's
death penalty has been approved by the Higher Court of the city
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, four members of Yan's trafficking clique, all women,
also received imprisonment terms ranging from 12 years to eight
years, plus sums of fines.
</P>
<P>
According to the court, the five-member group trafficked 12
boys in Chongqing between May 1996 and February 1998. Of the
kids, 10 were sold to eastern Fujian Province, some 1,200 km away
from their home.
</P>
<P>
Yan alone was directly involved in 11 of the 12 traffickings,
the court said. 
