<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao's Renewal to International Conventions Agreed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Officials of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group (JLG) made
these announcement here on Thursday after concluding a two-day
meeting on the renewal of Macao's member status to some
international bodies and the continuation of world conventions
applicable to Macao.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xi'an, representative of the Chinese side of the JLG,
said that the consensus was reached very quickly after reviewing
the list of about 200 international conventions applicable to
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Among the agreed some 80 conventions, some have already been
effective in Macao and some are still not, but will after 1999,
Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed that consultation on the international
convention issue should be completed basically by the end of the
year so that the re-registration procedure can be started next
year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the talks on Macao's member status to some
international organizations after 1999 has also entered its final
stage and is expected to complete this year.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese side has provided the Chinese side with a list
of international organizations that Macao hopes to join in before
the handover in 1999. It contains less than 10 organizations.
</P>
<P>
"We will make further studies of the list," Wang told
reporters on Thursday. "The Chinese side will support the entry so
long as it is necessary for Macao and benefits Macao."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Wang said that the two sides reached consensus at
the meeting on Macao's entry into four international bodies after
1999. They include two on bank supervision, one on moneywashing,
and one on a world sports body. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
