<HEADLINE> ADB Plans to Loan Vietnam 350 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
plans to loan Vietnam 350 million U.S. dollars, Vietnam News
Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be channeled to four projects: the reform of
state-run industrial enterprises, the upgrading of the national
highway, the rural credit project and the Mekong sub-region
cooperation program.
</P>
<P>
ADB will provide Vietnam with 12 technical assistance grants with
a combined value of about eight million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, ADB has provided Vietnam with loans of nearly 1.3
billion dollars for 19 projects and 72 technical assistance grants
with a combined value of 53.7 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to an ADB project expert, Vietnam has so far
disbursed over 275 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
