<HEADLINE> Slovenia Eyes EU Membership by 2003 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Slovenian President Milan Kucan said
here Thursday that he is expecting his country to join the
European Union (EU) by the year 2003.
</P>
<P>
Such a prospect was also mentioned by German leaders including
Chancellor Helmut Kohl and Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel whom he
met Wednesday, Kucan said.
</P>
<P>
While the EU membership would remain a political priority of
Slovenia, it was also in the interests of the EU to embrace the
politically stable Slovenia, Kucan said.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of 15 EU countries decided at their summit last
December to open membership negotiations with six nations: Poland,
Hungary, the Czech Republic, Slovenia, Estonia and Cyprus. 
</P>
