<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Party Leaders Discuss Economic Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- A group of non-communist party
leaders attended today's discussion on the country's economic
situation and its future development with the background of the
current financial turmoils in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The panel was sponsored by the United Front Work Department of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The discussion was attended by Member of the Political Bureau
of the CPC Central Committee and Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao and
presided over by Wang Zhaoguo, Vice-Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference and head of the department.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the end of the discussion, Wen said that the
crucial task at the present is to implement the principles set by
the CPC Central Committee and the State Council, in order to
maintain the current trend of the sound economic development and
to ensure the year's target of an eight-percent economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Measures should be taken to promote domestic market demands,
increase investment and readjust its structure, guide local
consumers to spend more money and consume more reasonably,
increase exports, and safeguard the balance of payment and a
stable Chinese currency, RMB yuan, the vice premier noted.
</P>
<P>
Wen stressed the importance of preventing financial hazards,
reforming the banking sector, and improving financial services.
</P>
