<HEADLINE> HK Summer Youth Program Enters 30th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's 30th Summer Youth
Program on the theme "Hong Kong, Our Home - Let's Serve and Share"
would be launched in July this year to bring young people aged six
to 25 a joyful and meaningful summer, it was announced here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The highlight of this year's program would be on the community
service aspect, with particular emphasis on services to the
disabled, elderly living on their own and new arrivals from
China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here on Thursday, Norman Lo,
chairman of the Summer Youth Program (SYP) Committee, said SYP
entered its 30th anniversary in 1998 since its founding in 1969.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, more than 15,000 activities were organized for
1,1170,000 participants, he said.
</P>
<P>
The 1998 SYP budget amounted to 63 million HK dollars (8.08
million U.S. dollars), of which 19 million HK dollars (2.44
million U.S. dollars) was contributed by the Hong Kong Jockey Club
Charities Trust and the balance was covered by relevant government
departments, the Provisional District Boards and corporate
sponsors.
</P>
<P>
The press conference was followed by an oath-taking ceremony
for district volunteers and members of the Power of Youth, which
comprised of outstanding young people who had taken part in past
SYP activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
