an anti-pollution ship from Britain to suck and dilute oil on sea
surface, according to the Arab daily Al Charq Al Awsat.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Istanbul Stock Exchange National-100 index dropped
278.09 points Wednesday from that of Tuesday to close at 3,666.85
due to worries arising from the steep fall of Russia's major
shares and Turkey's flooding, Daily News reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Many traders were very cautious in Wednesday's trading because
they feared the turmoil on Russia's stock market and the damaging
floods sweeping northwestern Turkey last weekend would bring a
negative impact on Turkish economy, financial experts here said.
</P>
