from Yingkou in Liaoning Province to Japan, according to the plan.
</P>
<P>
Yingkou Port will be designated as the transshiping port
the coordinated transport.
</P>
<P>
Transport Experts agreed that the move will promote cargo
transport between northeast China regions and coastal areas. With
high efficiency, low costs and convenient facilities, coordinated
transport service will also help promote economic development
in these areas. 
