<HEADLINE> Localities Urged to Be Prepared for Severe Floodings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The National Anti-Flooding and
Drought Headquarters issued a circular today ordering localities
to be prepared for the possible attacks of severe flooding.
</P>
<P>
The flooding season has arrived earlier than normal
years as heavy rainstorms have attacked part of the country, the
notice says, disclosing that 18 provinces and autonomous regions
have so far been hit by floods.
</P>
<P>
The circular says that leading officials of local
governments at all levels should take the responsibility for
anti-flooding, while measures must be taken to step up vigilance,
repair and check up dikes and dams, work out anti-flooding schemes
and enhance readiness.
</P>
<P>
Special attention should be paid to anti-flooding work on
small and medium-sized rivers and reservoirs, it says. 
</P>
</TEXT>
