<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 12:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills 2 Israeli Soldiers in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli soldiers were killed
by a roadside bomb in south Lebanon late Wednesday night and
Hezbollah guerillas have claimed responsibility, Israel Radio
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The two 20-year-old soldiers were taking part in a united
military action in the Israeli self-declared security zone in
south Lebanon when the bomb exploded, the radio said. Two other
soldiers were wounded.
</P>
<P>
This brought to six the number of Israeli soldiers who have
been killed since the beginning of the year. Nine Israeli-allied
South Lebanon Army militiamen have also been killed during the
period.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted military sources as saying that the bomb was
apparently detonated from a distance. It said Hezbollah guerillas
have claimed responsibility for the bomb explosion.
</P>
<P>
The incident followed four straight days of Israeli air raids
in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Senior Israeli military officials warned of a further
deterioration in the area, linking increasing Hezbollah activities
in the area with the municipal elections being held in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah is leading a guerrilla war in south Lebanon in a bid
to drive the 2,000 Israeli soldiers from the country.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up the 1,200-square-kilometer security zone in south
Lebanon in 1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its northern
areas from Lebanese guerrilla cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
