<HEADLINE> Economic Goals Will Be Reached This Year, Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji told over 2,600
junior and senior officials here today that China's economic
growth goals this year will be realized through the combined
efforts of the Chinese people and the principles and policies of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and the State
Council.
</P>
<P>
In a speech to the officials who are studying at the Party
School of the CPC Central Committee, Premier Zhu called the
country's economic situation good, in general, and basically
normal, although there are certain problems, mainly caused by the
current financial turmoil in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also explained the agricultural and industrial situation,
especially the state sector, and foreign trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
