<HEADLINE> CCF Donations to Earthquake Victims Total Ten Million Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"This is the biggest donation the CCF has made since its
founding in 1994," CCF Vice-President Wu Jianguo told the press
this evening.
</P>
<P>
After the earthquake, he said, the CCF has launched a series of
charity activities, and so far, they have received from domestic
and foreign institutions and individuals donations totaling 9.49
million yuan, plus various goods worth one million.
</P>
<P>
The CCF has installed 100 temporary classrooms for primary and
middle school children in the area, and rebuilt two permanent
schools and a home for the elderly, he added.
</P>
<P>
Wu said, charity is still new in China, but it has already got
strong support from people throughout the country and all over the
world. It will its priority to help the layoffs and the disabled,
he added.
</P>
<P>
At a charity dance performance sponsored by the CCF this
evening, it also received a donation of 500,000 yuan from the
Beijing branch of the Guangdong Development Bank and several other
enterprises as a fund for poverty relief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
