<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 1.17 Percent Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong shares Thursday fell
105.49 points, or 1.17 percent, to close at 8,877.94, the lowest
in four months.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index has dropped for five trading days
in a row, losing a total of 792 points, or 8.2 percent. Shares
plunged nearly 500 points Wednesday to hit a record low of
8,983.43 points in the Year of Tiger, the Chinese lunar year,
which began on January 28, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 7.305 billion H.K. dollars (936 million U.S.
dollars) on Thursday, down slightly from the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Property stocks were hit hardest, diving 325.09 points, or 3.04
percent. Bank, commerce and industry shares all dipped more than
one percent, but utilities stocks managed to edge up 7.52 points,
or 0.07 percent.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip index opened lower Thursday, but regained
strength in the morning session to finish at 9,065.25 points at
midday. When the market reopened in the afternoon, shares began to
lose ground and failed to climb up to the 9,000-point level before
close. 
</P>
</TEXT>
