<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola to Develop Mineral Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Angola is striving to develop its
own mineral industry, so as to reduce the dependency on imported
materials for its national industry.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Sumbula, Deputy Minister of Geology and Mines, said
here recently that the country has the capacity to produce all
the industrial materials which has for long been heavily relied
on importation.
</P>
<P>
He said things like bentunite and barita and some other
building materials, which have been imported from abroad, are
actually accessible in the country.
</P>
<P>
Angola has almost all the minerals like iron, copper, diamond,
zinc and quartz, waiting to be developed, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government has decided to open the mine inspection field
to private sectors, and is planning to take reasonable measures
for the development of the mines, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sumbula said that another important policy is to attract
foreign investment to join the Angolan enterprises for the
mineral industry development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
