<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EC Finances Uganda's Forestry Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
executive body of the European Union, has donated 1.5 million
U.S. Dollars to finance Uganda's forestry sector.
</P>
<P>
EC forest project officer Tony Finch was quoted by Thursday's
Monitor daily as saying that the money will be used to conserve
and manage forest reserves in Uganda over the next 12 years.
</P>
<P>
He said most of the money would be spent on forests like
Budongo, Bushenyi, Mabira, Moroto and those under Uganda national
parks management.
</P>
<P>
EC senior Rural Development Councillor Otto Moller said the
commission has revised its approach for tropical forests.
</P>
<P>
Over the last decade, Uganda has received some 15 million
Dollars from EC for development and conservation of forests, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The EC senior official said the new approach was made in
response to the declining acreage and quality of tropical
forests, environmental degradation, loss of biodiversity,
climatic changes and loss of cultural assets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
