<HEADLINE> Jinma Oilfield In Liaoning Listed in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The 180 million A-shares of the
Liaohe Jinma Oil Field Corporation, Ltd. were listed on the
Shenzhen Stock Exchange today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 117.54 million shares changed hands today, closing
at 5.85 yuan per share, up 51.29 percent from the issue price.
</P>
<P>
The Liaohe Oil Field in Liaoning Province, China's third
largest oil and natural gas producer, has 81.82 percent stock
rights of the listed company. The oil field pumps one-tenth of the
nation's annual production, and is now capable of producing 15
million tons of crude oil and 1.7 billion cubic meters of gas a
year.
</P>
<P>
The corporation, formed mainly by two of the oil field's
subsidiary oil businesses, issued 200 million A-shares in early
April to raise 749 million yuan, which will be used for oil and
gas exploration projects in the area.
</P>
<P>
The corporation's board predicts 366 million yuan in profits
this year.
</P>
<P>
Liaohe floated the second oil A-share on the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange after the Shengli Oil Field. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
