<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Thursday due to
continued negative perception of the local and regional economic
situation.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index shed 7.54
points to 544.74, the all-share Emas Index shed 1.81 points to
137.55, the Industrial Index lost 25.60 points to 1,039.28 and the
Second Board Index shed 1.22 points to 111.44.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 395 to 178 while 170 counters were
unchanged and 192 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 114.767 million shares valued
at 235.932 million ringgit (about 61.28 million U.S. dollars) from
90.107 million shares valued at 214.931 million ringgit (about
55.826 million U.S. dollars) traded on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main board increased to 104.227 million shares
valued at 220.660 million ringgit (about 57.31 million U.S.
dollars) from Wednesday's 82.441 million shares valued at 201.091
million ringgit (about 52.23 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the second board, turnover increased to 10.540 million
shares worth 15.272 million ringgit (about 3.966 million U.S.
dollars) from 7.666 million shares valued at 13.840 million
ringgit (about 3.594 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals increased to 9.089 million shares valued at
21.544 million ringgit (about 5.595 million U.S. dollars) from
1.507 million shares valued at 11.836 million ringgit (about 3.074
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
An analyst said investors continued to stay away from the
market as there is a general perception that things may not get
better in the near term as reflected by most of the major regional
bourses and local sentiment is dampened by the prospect of lower
economic growth in Malaysia this year than forecast earlier.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 8.247
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
13.053 million shares, construction 10.468 million shares,
trading/service 28.502 million shares, infrastructure 662,000
shares, finance 19.078 million shares, hotels 195,000 shares,
properties 11.466 million shares, plantation 2.448 million shares,
mining 1.995 million shares, trusts 56,000 shares, closed/fund
36,000 shares and loans 8.021 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
