<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Reports 10 Percent Rise in Bankruptcies in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The number of bankruptcies continued
to rise at a record-setting pace in Germany after showing a 10
percent increase in the first quarter of this year, the German
statistics office in Wiesbaden said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics released by the office, the
number of new bankruptcies reached 8,677 cases in the first three
months, including 6,304 cases in western Germany and 2,373 cases
in eastern Germany.
</P>
<P>
If such trend continued, Germany's bankruptcy total would set a
new record after the latest one of 33,398 cases in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
