<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Abduct School Boys </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Five Tamil school boys have been
abducted by the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) in North
Central Province of sri Lanka, police sources here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the boys were fishing in a lake at Bowatta in
Polonnaruwa District, 220 kilometers from here Wednesday evening,
when a group LTTE rebels arrived. All five boys were between 12
and 14 years of age.
</P>
<P>
The parents of the children had made complaints at local police
who are investigating, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Only two weeks ago, LTTE leaders assured the visiting United
Nations special envoy on Children and Armed Conflict Olara Otunnu
that children would not be recruited.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a 15-year war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
