<HEADLINE> Six Die of Flood, Accident in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Six persons died of flood and
traffic accident in Makwanpur district about 70 kilometers south
of Kathmandu, police sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Four including three members of a family were swept away
Tuesday in the village of Namatar by flood caused by heavy
rainfall. The accident occurred when they were returning home from
a religious function held in the neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, two others died when they jumped off a speeding
bus due to fear of an accident after the steering of the bus broke
off all of a sudden, the police sources said. 
</P>
