<HEADLINE> ITE HK '98 Still Strong Force in Travel Industry: Tung Chee Hwa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The International Travel Expo
(ITE) Hong Kong '98 remains a strong force in the travel industry
both in Hong Kong and Asia, Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, said in his message to
the ITE HK '98, which opened here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue to be the crossroads of the East and West
where visitors from all over the world for business or leisure and
we will continue to invest in our infrastructure and take the
necessary measures to ensure adequate support to our positions as
a leading tourist destination and aviation center in the region,"
he said in the message.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event in the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center is the largest in scale in Asia and the first ITE to be
held since Hong Kong's handover last July.
</P>
<P>
Despite the economic difficulties and downturn affecting the
travel industry in Asia, the organizers of the 12th annual event
managed to maintain the size and scale of ITE HK '98. Some 500
exhibitors from 50 countries and regions around the world are
attending this year's Travel Expo.
</P>
<P>
The organizers managed to make ITE more practical and useful
this year, focusing on issues that will help people do business.
For the first time, ITE will also emphasize business travel,
Corporate users had been invited to the exhibition during the two
trade days while business travel seminars were included in the
One-site Forum.
</P>
<P>
ITE, together with sponsors and supporters, is hosting 350
international buyers from around the world with 1,000 local buyers
already registered and many more are expected, according to the
organizers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
