<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Conduct Crackdown on Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government has
planned to conduct a combing operation soon to crackdown on
terrorists across the country, a press report said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A list of three categories of terrorists has been prepared by
the law enforcing agencies to nab the miscreants, the report
quoted a senior police official as saying.
</P>
<P>
The decision for the crackdown which might start from the next
month came following an alarming rise of crimes, including murder,
rape and extortion, posing serious threat to the security of the
people, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
Police were concerned about recent increase in the number of
terrorist activities in the capital of Dhaka and also across the
country.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of terrorists were arrested in the country in the
past two years, the official said. "But most of them were released
on bail and they again got involved in crimes," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
