<HEADLINE> International Efforts Urged for South Asia Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- China today urged the international
community to make concerted efforts and take a common stand to
stabilize the situation in South Asia after India's nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
The comments were made by Zhu Bangzao, spokesman for China's
Ministry of Foreign Affairs, in the routine news briefing.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that India is held solely responsible for the current
instable situation in South Asia. "In disregard of the opposition
from the international community, India wantonly conducted nuclear
test, posing a threat to neighboring countries," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"It is imperative for the international community to take
common action in the effort to prompt India to abandon its nuclear
weapons development program and change its wrong stance in this
regard," Zhu noted.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the view that only in this way can the worries of
nations in the region about their security be eliminated.  
</P>
