<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysian Researchers Discover New Method to Kill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Researchers at Malaysian
Science University have found a method to eradicate fruit flies
using the synthetic sex pheromone technique, the university's
Biological Science Studies Center Lecturer Prof. Tan Keng Hong
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The synthetic sex pheromone, produced from the chemical Methyl
Eugonole, was similar to that secreted by the male flies and could
be used to attract female fruit flies to a spot making it easier
for the insects to be exterminated, he said after attending the
opening of the five-day Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO)
and the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) international
conference in Pulau Pinang, northwestern Malaysia, Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Pheromones are natural substances produced by plants and its
odour can be picked up by insects which are attracted to it," he
was quoted by Malaysia's national news agency Bernama as saying.
</P>
<P>
Tan said research on the synthetic sex pheromone technique was
started some four years ago and the method was still on trial.
</P>
<P>
He said spraying the fruits with pesticides or covering them
had been found not to be effective in preventing attacks by fruit
flies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
