<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Bomb Detected, Another Blasted in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The telecom facilities in the Sri
Lanka appear to be a prime target of some hidden hand manipulating
under cover as one bomb was detected in the nick of time at the
Ratnapura complex at dawn Thursday, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the bomb weighed one-and-half kilograms which
will be planned damaged the complexes of the Ratnapura town, over
100 kilometers from Colombo.
</P>
<P>
There had been a blast almost at the same time on a transformer
in Dehiwela at 4:30 Thursday. The transformer was damaged, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
They noted investigators are examining whether this also had
any connection to other bombs that had exploded earlier.
</P>
<P>
The Ratnapura complex bomb was detected by a policeman at the
guard room of the telecom complex. He heard some unusual noise
from the direction of the main buildings. When he approached the
complex to have a closer look, a man was seen hurriedly leaving
the scene. But there was no time for him to apprehend the
intruder.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the policeman brought this to the notice of
the army unit, who came to the scene and searched the building
minutely.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was discovered and a major blast was fortunately
averted.
</P>
<P>
Top level investigators suspect that this chain of explosions
to be inside jobs, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth bomb to be planted exclusively in
telecommunication sites. Three previous bombs exploded and
seriously damaged the telecom building in kalutara, kuliyapitiya
and Nochchiyagama in the month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
