<HEADLINE> China to Build More Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- China plans to build
1,200 kilometers of expressways this year and 4,000 km more in
the coming three years, an official with the Ministry of
Communications said today.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the country had 4,735 km of
expressways.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has recently decided to increase
investment in infrastructural construction to keep pace with
economic development.
</P>
<P>
According to a new plan, China will invest 160 billion yuan
this year in highway construction, 40 billion yuan more than in
an original plan.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be used to build 24,500 km of highways, which
will bring the total mileage of the country's highways to 1.25
million km by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The investment for the next three years is expected to amount
to 500 billion yuan, said the official.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the annual expressway construction
surpassed 1,000 km in China.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are also considering new plans for expressway
construction. Liaoning, Shanxi and Hebei provinces and the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region have committed several billion yuan to
expressway construction this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
