programs overseas including in France and we plan to send them for
longer training in future," he told reporters after visiting the
French Navy vessel "FNS Siroco" which called at West Port, Port
Klang about 33 kilometers Southwest from here.
</P>
<P>
The ship, which is part of the French Rapid Deployment Force,
is on a five-day goodwill visit. An exhibition on some of the most
advanced French military equipment is also being held on board the
ship and is open to the public Friday, the last day of the visit.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister said a French Navy Officer from the Rapid
Deployment Force would be attached to the Defense Ministry for two
months to conduct training, which he said was an effort by both
countries to strengthen further the existing defense cooperation
between Malaysia and France.
</P>
<P>
Syed Hamid said he would attend the five-day French Defense
Exhibition to be held in Paris from June 2. 
