<HEADLINE> hke052831-Philippine Speaker Concedes Defeat in Presidential Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Philippine House Speaker Jose de
Venecia Thursday conceded defeat to Vice President Joseph Estrada
in the May 11 presidential race.
</P>
<P>
De Venecia, anointed by President Fidel Ramos as the standard
bearer of the ruling Lakas-NUCD party, is the last among the nine
presidential candidates to concede defeat.
</P>
