<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 28 (Xinhua) -- A total of 20 rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the military
operations staged by the Turkish security forces in southeastern
Turkey, said an official statement issued on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the Turkish government troops had wiped out 17 PKK
militants in the Akcabudak and Alicliyayla areas of Lice town in
Diyarbakir province and three in Gurpinar town of Van province
linking neighboring Iran.
</P>
<P>
However, the statement failed to disclose when the PKK rebels
were killed.
</P>
<P>
It said that the security forces had captured three PKK
guerrillas in Cinar town of Diyarbakir.
</P>
<P>
One soldier was killed and two others were wounded in the
two-hour clash between the PKK and the security forces in the
Gurpinar town, according to Turkey's semi-official Anatolia news
agency.
</P>
<P>
More than 35,000 people, including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops, have been killed in conflicts since the PKK
started the separatist war for autonomy in southeastern Turkey in
August, 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
