<HEADLINE> Swimming School Named after Olympic Champion Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAODING, North China, May 28 (Xinhua) -- A swimming school
named after China's former world and Olympic champion Qian Hong
opened here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The swimming school, established as a joint-stock venture, aims
at training promising young swimmers while at the same time
providing them education in an all-in-one system from kindergarten
to high school.
</P>
<P>
The school, which boasts an Olympic size and a 25x16 meters
indoor pool, is not only opened to Chinese but also to overseas
children.
</P>
<P>
Qian, winner of the women's 100 meter butterfly at the world
championships in 1991 and the Olympic Games in 1992, raised part
of the fund for the school by selling her Olympic gold medal.
</P>
