<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed higher in Tokyo
Thursday, recouping part of the previous day's 220.53-point loss.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected First Section issues on
the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 132.26 points or 0.84 percent from
Wednesday's close to finish at 15,796.55.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, added 1.39 points or 0.11 percent to 1,223.73.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section stayed thin at an estimated 320 million
shares, unchanged from Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ishikawa Seisakusho was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
A jump on the futures market prompted arbitrage-linked buying, with
the June Nikkei futures climbing 160 points to close at 15,760,
traders said.
</P>
<P>
Upturns from recent plunges in the key composite stock price index
on the Seoul bourse and the Hang Seng Index of Hong Kong stocks helped
boost Nikkei futures prices, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,331 issues listed on the First Section, gainers
outnumbered losers 665 to 407, with 165 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
