<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to decline
sharply on the Singapore Market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index lost another 33.91 points to close at 1261.62
points on Thursday
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 65.14 million units, valued
at 91.04 million Singapore dollars (about 54.51 million U.S.
dollars). Declines led advances by 146 to 69, while 377 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 10.34 million units. It was followed by
DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Land which had 9.96 million
shares traded. TAC 200 was next with 7.31 million units changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Guinness led the gainers of the day as it rose by 20 cents to
finish at 2.5 Singapore dollars. TAC 200 increased by 13 cents to
end at 1.5 U.S. dollars. Asia Pacific Brew was up by 12 cents to
close at 4.4 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, local computer sound card maker Creative 50
was the biggest loser as it declined by 1.4 dollars to end at 30.6
Singapore dollars. SPH (Singapore Press Holdings) fell by 70 cents
to close at 13.6 Singapore dollars, while Seaview was down by 30
cents to finish at 4.2 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
