<HEADLINE> Books Mark 20th Anniversary of Reform, Opening-Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- More than 80 kinds of books will be
published later this year to mark the 20th anniversary of the
reform and opening-up which was initiated in 1978.
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Press and Publications
Administration said that the topics of these books vary from local
practices to background and the process of the reform and
opening-up in China.
</P>
<P>
The books will include one about a foreigner's views on China's
reform and opening-up, one on China's rural reform and the whole
reform and opening-up process, and a reference book on big events
that happened in the last 20 years.
</P>
<P>
At a recent meeting, Yang Muzhi, vice director of the State
Press and Publications Administration, asked all the relevant
publication houses not to seek only their own economic returns
when publishing these books.
</P>
<P>
"Quality of publication should be put in first place," he said.
</P>
<P>
The reform and opening-up policy was initiated in 1978 at the
Third Plenary Session of the 11th Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China. Since then, great changes have taken
place in China and significant progress in all aspects have been
made.
</P>
<P>
China will hold a series of activities, such as picture
exhibitions and seminars, to mark the 20th anniversary of the
reform and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
Today's People's Daily (overseas edition) published the first
part of achievements made by China's provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions during the past 20 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
