<HEADLINE> Shanxi Volunteers to Solicit Donations for Project Hope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, May 28 (Xinhua) -- One hundred volunteers in north
China's Shanxi Province will solicit donations for "Project Hope,"
a nationwide educational program to help school dropouts return
to school.
</P>
<P>
The donations will be used to help school dropouts in Shanxi's
15 poverty-stricken counties receive education and hold
training programs for their teachers.
</P>
<P>
The province initiated the Project Hope in 1990. To date, it has
received more than 40 million yuan in donations from all walks of
life. The funds have helped 44,000 dropouts return to school, set
up 260 primary schools, established 248 libraries for pupils, and
bought 400,000 study aids.
</P>
<P>
The current donation management system is complicated for
people who are willing to donate to the project, a local education
official said.
</P>
<P>
The volunteers with certificates of special training will
provide a convenient way for people to donate in their place of
work or at home.  
</P>
