<HEADLINE> British Companies Open Paint Plant in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 28 (Xinhua) -- ICI Swire Paints (Shanghai) Ltd.,
a British venture, went into operation earlier this week in the
Songjiang Industrial Area in Shanghai, China's largest commercial
and industrial center.
</P>
<P>
Funded by chemical giant ICI Group and the Swire Group, both of
Britain, the factory has a designed annual production capacity of
35 million liters of construction paint.
</P>
<P>
It is ICI Group's first factory to adopt a fully automated
paint production line. The factory is equipped with first-class
waste-treatment facilities.
</P>
<P>
Established 72 years ago, the ICI Group has opened 59 factories
in 26 countries, with a total paint output of 1.13
billion liters in 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to ICI sources, the group has given a high priority
to the Asian market. As early as in 1989, subsidiary ICI Paints
and the Swire Group invested 24 million U.S. dollars to open a
paint factory in Guangzhou. 
