<P>
All the main leaders weakened. Fletcher Building shares were
the hardest hit, diving 14 cents to 300 cents. Air New Zealand and
Fletcher Energy lost 5 cents each to 197 cents and 595 cents
respectively. Brierley Investment fell another 3 cents to 90
cents. Carter Holt Harvey shed 8 cents to 232 cents. Lion Nathan
dipped 6 cents to 460 cent. And Telecom slipped 7 cents to 858
cents.
</P>
<P>
On the overall market, falls outnumbered rises by 84 to 19.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
