<HEADLINE> Bulls Beat Pacers 106-87 in NBA Playoff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Chicago Bulls gained a swift
victory Wednesday night by beating Indiana Pacers 106-87 in the
NBA playoff to take a 3-2 lead in the Eastern Conference finals.
</P>
<P>
Michael Jordan and Scottie Pippen led the Bulls to overpower
the Pacers in the first half and there was no let-up in the second
half.
</P>
<P>
Jordan scored 29 points with seven rebounds and four assists as
he led the team in scoring for the 13th time in 13 playoff games.
</P>
<P>
Pippen finished with 20 points, eight rebounds and seven
assists and Toni Kukoc added 19 points as the Bulls avoided their
first three-game losing streak with Jordan on the team since the
fall of 1990.
</P>
<P>
The two teams will meet at Game 6 on Friday night. The Bulls
will be looking to clinch their third straight trip to the NBA
Finals and a possible sixth championship title this decade.
</P>
<P>
Chicago opened a 29-16 lead after first quarter, holding
Indiana without a field goal for more than 14 minutes. The Bulls
also held the Pacers to 34 percent shooting and allowed Indiana to
make only 23 field goals.
</P>
<P>
Pippen, who averaged 15 in the first four games of the series,
made an outstanding contribution of 17 points for the Bulls by
half-time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
