<HEADLINE> Hand-held Computer Sales Up 65 Percent Worldwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Sales of hand-held computers
increased 65 percent worldwide in 1997, said Dataquest, a market
research group based in the Silicon Valley in California.
</P>
<P>
Driven by falling prices and improved functioning, total
shipments of hand-held computer reached 2.4 million units last
year, according to a Dataquest survey released Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hand-held computers are a group of portable machines generally
used as portable calendars, address books or note pads, and are
most often purchased by individual business professionals.
</P>
<P>
At present, 3Com and Hewlett-Packard are the top vendors of
hand-held computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
