<HEADLINE> Dengue Fever, Encephalitis Spreading in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 27 (xinhua) -- Dengue fever and encephalitis have
killed dozens of Vietnamese people as the diseases spread across
the country, the Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Dengue fever spread to 40 provinces with over 22,300 cases
reported so far this year, a 68 percent increase over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
An Giang province in the south was the hardest hit, with 25
deaths attributed to the fatal diseases.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, about 500 cases of encephalitis, including Japanese
B encephalitis, have been reported in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese Health Ministry said that 17 people, out of the
total 500 dengue patients, died of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam can produce vaccines against the Japanese B type
encephalitis, but the quantity produced has not been sufficient to
meet the country's demand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
