<HEADLINE> Venezuela Bank Head Urges Watch on Money Laundering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 27 (Xinhua) -- The president of the Banco
Industrial de Venezuela, Rafael Pena Alvarez, Wednesday urged all
people working in that bank to "be ready for the struggle" against
the laundering of money gained from narcotics trafficking.
</P>
<P>
In a communique directed at all workers, he asked employees to
work harder in order to solidify the banking institution.
</P>
<P>
Among points he specified was the revision of regulations
involving the legitimacy of assets.
</P>
<P>
The Banco Industrial president issued his document following
the results of investigations by United States authorities on the
laundering of money derived from "narcotraffic" operations.
</P>
<P>
A press bulletin of the U.S. Federal Reserve claimed five
officers from Venezuelan banks in the United States were
incriminated in money laundering activities amounting to 9.5
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The alleged operation had been performed through four
Venezuelan banks, one of them the Banco Industrial de Venezuela,
the bulletin said. 
