<HEADLINE> Chile's Air Freight Triples in 10 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Chilean air freight has tripled in
the past 10 years, from 63,615 tons in 1988 to 213,611 tons in
1997, Chile's Civil Aeronautical Board says.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean Lan Chile airline has maintained its leadership in
the past 10 years, carrying 58 percent of the total freight in
1997.
</P>
<P>
The main destinations of Chilean air flights are the United
States, Argentina, Brazil and some European countries.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Transport predicts that air freight will reach
300,000 tons at the end of the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
