<DOCNO> XIE19980528.0285 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Stable Growth in Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- China's stock market showed stable
development in the first four months of this year, with market
capitalization up 18.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Composite Index of the Shanghai Stock Exchange
closed at 1,343 points on April 30, up 12 percent from the start
of this year, according to the latest statistics of the China
Securities Regulatory Commission, the industry watchdog.
</P>
<P>
The key index of the nation's other stock exchange in the
southern special economic zone of Shenzhen finished April at 4,180
points, almost unchanged from the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
China's stock market capitalization surged 18.7 percent in the
four-month period to more than 2.08 trillion yuan. Earlier
commission figures indicated that China now has more than 34
million stock market investors.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, China issued 39 A shares, four B shares
and three H shares in the January-April period. "A" shares refer
to those issued by Chinese companies for domestic investors only;
"B" shares are those issued in China but reserved for overseas
investors; and "H" shares refer to those issued in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The issues raised funds worth 29.4 billion yuan in aggregate,
with A-share issues and their rights issues pooling 24.9 billion
yuan, a jump of 33 percent from the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months, China also issued its first three
securities investment funds valued at 2 billion yuan each. The
funds, all closed-end, have met with significant investor
enthusiasm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
