<HEADLINE> Norway Blanks Nine-Man Saudi Arabia 6-0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSLO, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Norway blanked Saudi Arabia 6-0 in a
World Cup warm-up match on Wednesday in Molde, Norway, but the
match was almost ruined by the send-off of two Saudi players.
</P>
<P>
Goalkeeper Mohammed Al-Daye and Mohammed Al-Khlaiwi were sent
off by Danish referee Knud Erik Fisker for fouls on Norway's Ole
Gunnar Solskjaer in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The victory extended Norway's unbeaten run to 14 games dated
back to January 1997 and unbeaten at home since 1991.
</P>
<P>
Vidar Riseth scored on a penalty, beating substitute goalkeeper
Hussein Al-Sadiq who dashed toward the wrong way.
</P>
<P>
The starting keeper Al-Daye was expelled in an earlier 19th
minute goalmouth scramble,
</P>
<P>
Solskjaer, Manchester United's striker, scored a double to put
the hosts to a 3-0 lead at break.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Egil Ostenstad, Tore Andre Flo and Roar Strand
finished with three goals in the last ten minutes of the game.
</P>
<P>
Norway faces reigning champions Brazil, Scotland and Morocco in
the same group in the first round at the World Cup next month.
</P>
</TEXT>
