<HEADLINE> MERCOSUR Countries Call for More Security Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Interior ministers of the
Southern Common Market (MERCOSUR) ended their two-day meeting here
on Wednesday with a call for greater security cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Bolivian and Chilean interior ministers also joined the four
ministers of MERCOSUR, a regional commercial bloc grouping
Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay and Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
Emphasizing the importance of security among their countries,
the ministers declared that the security issue is a common
challenge for the region and the continent.
</P>
<P>
They discussed plans to sign cooperative security agreements
such as a protocol on mutual juridical assistance in criminal
affairs. They also agreed to conclude immediately a common treaty
on extradition of criminals.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the ministers agreed to create a regional office
to register the sale and purchase of firearms, ammunitions,
explosives and other related materials.
</P>
<P>
Police and security officers also participated in the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
