<HEADLINE> First Foreign Airlines Hooked up to China's Air-Ticket System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 28 (Xinhua) -- Ansett Australia (AA) airlines
from Austria has become the first foreign carrier hooking up its
computing networks with China's air-ticket booking system.
</P>
<P>
Since Sunday, travel agencies in China can receive AA's
book-on-command service through the national network system
instead of calling its representative office here in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Australian company has also developed a terminal server for
emergency treatment of data errors and any problems in booking
tickets.
</P>
<P>
Ansett opened direct air service linking Shanghai and Sydney,
Australia, in June of 1997 with two flights a week. Six months
later, a third flight was added resulting from a skyrocketing
number of passengers on the route. 
</P>
