<HEADLINE> Monument, Statue Built To Mark Anti-Imperialism Movement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 28 (Xinhua) -- A marble monument and a bronze
statue have been built with funds from the municipal government of
Shanghai to mark the 73rd anniversary of the May 30 Movement.
</P>
<P>
The five-ton statue, which is three meters high and 6.78 meters
wide, has 65 figures. It contains the largest number of figures on
a bronze statue in the country, according to official sources. The
monument is 1 meter high and 5.4 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
The two memorial works will be placed in the Shanghai Longhua
Martyrs' Tomb by early July.
</P>
<P>
The movement began in Shanghai on May 30, 1925, when a local
factory worker was shot down by his Japanese boss. Hundreds of
thousands of local workers and peasants took to the streets
shouting slogans against imperialist suppression. 
</P>
</TEXT>
