<HEADLINE> China Issues White Paper on Development of Marine Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The Information Office of the State
Council today issued a white paper titled "the Development of
China's Marine Programs".
</P>
<P>
As the first of its kind on the marine programs issued by the
Chinese government, the white paper said that as a major
developing country with a long coastline, China attaches great
importance to marine development and protection, and takes it as
the state's development strategy.
</P>
<P>
The 12,000-character white paper has six parts
including sustainable marine development strategy; rational
development and utilization of marine resources; the protection
and preservation of the marine environment; the development of
oceanographic science, technology and education; the
implementation of comprehensive marine management, and
international cooperation in maritime affairs.
</P>
<P>
It said that the year 1998 has been designated by the United
Nations as the International Ocean Year and in the coming 21st
century mankind will have new opportunities to develop and
utilize the ocean.
</P>
<P>
It said that China has made positive contributions to
international ocean development and protection by participating
positively in UN marine affairs, promoting cooperation between
countries and regions and conscientiously carrying out its
obligations in this field.  
</P>
