<HEADLINE> Spain Beats China at Women's Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROTENBURG, Germany, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Ana Belen Alvaro scored
17 points, including five 3-pointers, to pace Spain to a 72-55 win
over China on Wednesday night at the Women's World Basketball
Championship here.
</P>
<P>
Like medal favorites Russians, who downed Argentina 107-32
early Wednesday, the Spainish won two straight victories and will
fight for the group A title against Russia Thursday night at
Meirotels-Hall, Rotenburg.
</P>
<P>
"I am very satisfied with the game, especially our defense,"
said Spain coach Manuel Coloma.
</P>
<P>
"The key to our success is our team spirit. With these kind of
players you can only win. Our captain Alvaro played sensational
game. Her three-pointer percent (5-7) was incredible."
</P>
<P>
Spain, which placed eighth four years ago in Sydney, Australia,
never looked back after Elisabeth Cebrian scored one of two free
throws which put the Spaniards 14-11 ahead 12 minutes into the
game.
</P>
<P>
After Spain concluded the first half 41-31, Alvaro scored two
3-pointers in a row to key Spain in a 16-5 run that allowed the
winner to build an edge as many as 21 points with 57-36, the
biggest gap in the game.
</P>
<P>
Three other players also scored double-figures with Anula
Nieves added 16 points, Pilar Alonso 12 and Marina Ferragut 11.
</P>
<P>
Miao Bo led the Chinese with nine points, followed by Ma
Chengqing.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Haixia, the defending Most Valuable Player at the last
championship, was a disappointment again, making off only two
points and three rebounds in 21 minutes.
</P>
<P>
"Our offense was not strong enough, especially in the first
half. Zheng Haixia, inspite of her injury and illness, gave her
best, but unfortunately with her two points in total, couldn't
come close to her normal performance level," said Chinese coach Ma
Yuenan,
</P>
<P>
Veteran Zheng Dongmei, who contributed six points, said her
team was still a young team and need time to gain experiences.
</P>
<P>
China takes on Argentina Thursday for third place in the group
with the winner entering the second round in Bremen along with
Russia and Spain.
</P>
<P>
The loser goes to Dessau for Classification matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
