<DOCNO> XIE19980528.0328 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Tea Exporter Expecting Higher Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, May 28 (Xinhua) -- The Wuyuan Tea Plant in southeast
Jiangxi Province, one of three tea-processing plants authorized to
conduct direct foreign trade in China, is preparing for an upturn
in its exports this year.
</P>
<P>
"The bustling scene in the workshop tells of brisk sales," the
head of the packaging department said, adding that contracts have
been flowing in one after another since Spring Festival in
February, months ahead of the Wuyuan's spring tea harvest.
</P>
<P>
At the East China Export Commodity Fair held in March, the
company closed deals for 883.2 tons. At the Chinese Export
Commodity Fair (CECF) in April, the company signed contracts for
1,210 tons, said Yu Xinchun, director of the plant.
</P>
<P>
According to Yu, Southeast Asia's financial turmoil has little
follow-up effect on China's tea exports. "We are expecting a
higher transaction figure in the autumn event of CECF," he said.
</P>
<P>
As the country's major green-tea cultivation center, Wuyuan
County has 10,666 hectares of tea growing area yielding 6,000
tons of output annually, with the export portion making up more
than 90 percent of its total sales.
</P>
<P>
The Wuyuan Tea Plant with an annual output of 5,000 tons has
more than 20 varieties. Green tea labeled with the brand "Wuyuan"
has gained reputation in markets both at home and abroad. It has
been honored in the U.S. book "Complete Collection of Tea" as an
elite green tea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980528.0329 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Pursues Sustainable Maritime Development Strategy (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In conducting international cooperation in maritime affairs,
the paper said that China has always supported and actively
participated in various forms of marine-related activities
promoted by the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
China has joined nearly 20 international organizations,
including the Intergovernmental Oceanographic Commission of the
United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization
(UNESCO/IOC), Scientific Committee on Oceanic Research (SCOR),
Commission on Maritime Meteorology(CMM), and International
Maritime Organization (IMO). China has also engaged extensively in
cooperation and exchanges in maritime affairs with scores of
countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that China has signed bilateral maritime
transportation agreements with 51 countries, making positive
efforts to promote international cooperation and exchanges in
maritime transportation. China has also acceded to 30-some
conventions formulated by the International Maritime Organization
(IMO).
</P>
<P>
China has also taken part in global oceanographic activities,
including the GSMMP (global studies and monitoring of marine
pollution), the TOGA (tropical ocean and global atmospheric
project), the WOCE (world ocean circulation experiment), making
positive efforts to promote worldwide oceanographic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The paper pointed out that China is clearly aware of the fact
that, as a developing country with inadequate level of development
and limited economic strength, China has lagged behind some of the
developed countries in this regard. Especially, the increasing
population and rapid economic growth in the coastal areas in
recent years have put great pressure on the marine environmental
protection and hampered the rational development of marine
resources.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that with the continuing growth of the forces of
social production, the further building-up of comprehensive
national strength and the gradual awakening of the people's
consciousness of the importance of marine protection, China's
marine programs will definitely enjoy still greater development.
</P>
<P>
Together with other countries and international organizations
concerned, China will, as always, play its part in bringing
mankind's work for marine development and protection onto the road
of sustainable development, the paper said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
