<HEADLINE> Russia Drubbs Argentina 107-32 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROTENBURG, Germany, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Russia created the
biggest scoring margin at the 13th Women's World Basketball
Championship by crushing Argentina 107-32 in Wednesday's group A
match here.
</P>
<P>
Russia, who beat China 70-52 last night, would top the group if
they beat Spain on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Russians, who scored 13 unanswered points just five minutes
into the game, proved they were too strong to overcome for the
smaller Argentines.
</P>
<P>
After leading the first half 40-21, Russia continued their
domination and used their bench players to extend the gap.
</P>
<P>
Russian had twice as much in rebounds at 46 and outclassed the
South American team with 49 percent against 20 percent in the
field goal percentage. 
</P>
