continue deepening their cooperative relationship, a joint
statement issued by the US-China Joint Economic Committee (JEC)
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two countries believe President Bill Clinton's upcoming
visit will help advance this aim, said the statement, issued at
the end of a one-day meeting of the JEC. It said a team from the
US Treasury Department would also visit China to discuss the
possibilities for increased cooperation.
</P>
<P>
-- A new set of regulations on individual housing mortgage
loans has recently been issued by the People's Bank of China to
facilitate the nation's housing reform and trigger a business boom
in the property market, according to an article in Financial
News. 
