<HEADLINE> Shanghai Site of International Business Symposium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 28 (Xinhua) -- China International Business
Symposium opened here Wednesday in Shanghai, the country's largest
commercial center.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 experts from a dozen countries and regions --
including the United States, Britain, Canada, and Austria -- are
attending the three-day symposium and will hold discussions on
China's recent economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
The experts also will be discussing the development of
international economy, trade, and finance.
</P>
<P>
The symposium has so far received 120 papers, 60 percent
written by foreign experts who agree that China now faces a sound
international business environment, which is profitable for its
further economic development and reform.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is being sponsored by the Shanghai Institute of
Finance and Economics and Hong Kong's Lingnan College.  
</P>
</TEXT>
