<HEADLINE> Aussies Top World Cup Hockey Group Preliminaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, May 27 (Xinhua) -- Olympic and World Cup champions
Australia scored their fifth straight win on Wednesday to top the
women's group A preliminaries of the World Cup Field Hockey
Tournament.
</P>
<P>
Nicole Mott scored a goal in each of the two halves while
Katrina Powell, Bianca Langham and Rechelle Hawkes contributed a
goal apiece to pace the Australians to a 5-2 win over South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Marilyn Agliotti and Susan Wessels scored for the South
Africans.
</P>
<P>
Germany nipped Scotland 1-0 to finish behind Australia in the
group. The top two teams enter the sudden-death semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Australia plays Argentina that scored four win against one draw
in the group B preliminaries while Germany takes on hosts the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch women finished atop group B also with four wins and
one draw but with favorable goal difference.
</P>
<P>
In other women's matches, New Zealand beat England 2-1; the
United States beat China 4-0; South Korea downed India 4-2, and
the Netherlands tied Argentina 2-2.
</P>
<P>
In the men's action of the day, cup holders Pakistan defeated
Poland 3-1; Spain blanked Malaysia with three unanswered goals;
Australia whitewashed England also 3-0.
</P>
<P>
Spain, Olympic silver medalists, is now strongly placed to
qualify for the men's semi-finals after Wednesday's win. The
Spaniards have not reached World Cup semi-finals since they were
beaten by Pakistan in 1971.
</P>
<P>
The men's group preliminaries conclude on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
